<li id="cite_note-22"><b><a href="#cite_ref-22" title="">^</a></b> The Forbidden City was listed as the "<a href="http://whc.unesco.org/archive/advisory_body_evaluation/439.pdf" class="external text" title="http://whc.unesco.org/archive/advisory_body_evaluation/439.pdf" rel="nofollow">Imperial Palace of the Ming and Qing Dynasties</a>" (<small>Official Document</small>). In 2004, <a href="/wiki/Mukden_Palace" title="Mukden Palace">Mukden Palace</a> in <a href="/wiki/Shenyang" title="Shenyang">Shenyang</a> was added as an extension item to the property, which then became known as "Imperial Palaces of the Ming and Qing Dynasties in Beijing and Shenyang": <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/439" class="external text" title="http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/439" rel="nofollow">"UNESCO World Heritage List: Imperial Palaces of the Ming and Qing Dynasties in Beijing and Shenyang"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/439" class="external free" title="http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/439" rel="nofollow">http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/439</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-05-04</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=UNESCO+World+Heritage+List%3A+Imperial+Palaces+of+the+Ming+and+Qing+Dynasties+in+Beijing+and+Shenyang&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwhc.unesco.org%2Fen%2Flist%2F439&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Forbidden_City"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
